Millet Kheer (pudding)

Yield:     2-4 servings
prep time: 5 min
cook time: 45 min

3c whole milk
1c millet
1/4c sugar
pinch ground cadamom
pinch saffron threads

In a medium saucepan over medium-high heat, combine the milk and millet and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to a simmer and stir in the sugar. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until the milk has absorbed and the mixture has become creamy, 40-45min. If the mixture looks dry, add 1/4c milk as needed until the millet is tender.
Stir in the cardamom and saffron and serve hot.
